{
  "texts": [
    "Suitable charging protocols are essential to extend the battery lifespan.",
    "However, the innovation of new materials will be detrimental to realizing the fast-charging capabilities.",
    "The interfacial resistance, the wettability of the cathode materials, the conductivity of the electrolytes, the deposition or insertion of ions in the anode, and the thermal stability are key features in determining the performance of the devices at extremely high current density.",
    "In terms of the optimization of charging protocols, Attia et al.",
    "97 developed a closed-loop optimization of fast-charging protocols for commercial high-power cylindrical cells."
  ]
}